In his remarks at the Panama Canal, Vice President Mike Pence addressed the recent terror attack in Barcelona, expressing condolences and pledging support to Spain. He then emphasized the importance of the U.S.-Panamanian relationship and the shared goals of security and prosperity. Pence praised the history and significance of the Panama Canal as a symbol of partnership between the two nations. He also highlighted the economic benefits of the canal's expansion and the potential for further trade and investment in the region. Pence mentioned ongoing efforts to renegotiate the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) and reiterated the Trump administration's commitment to free and fair trade. He urged Latin American countries to continue enacting economic reforms and emphasized the need for a peaceful resolution to the crisis in Venezuela. Pence concluded by expressing confidence in the future of the Western Hemisphere and the power of freedom to guide the nations in this New World.